The service suffered heavy delays after vandals damaged a large part of Metrorail&#8217;s infrastructure. CAPE TOWN - Metrorail has asked Western Cape commuters to make alternative transport arrangements for today as all train services have been suspended.Yesterday, the service suffered heavy delays after vandals damaged a large part of Metrorail s infrastructure.The rail operator says decided trains would not run today in the interest of passenger safety and security, allowing technicians to perform the necessary repairs.Metrorail's Riana Scott says: It is unfortunately quite time consuming. We are working hard to have it done by tomorrow morning so that we can have a normal peak hour service. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)